org.stekikun.dolmen.common

Class PList<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.stekikun.dolmen.common.PList<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the type of elements stored in the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<A>

    public final class PList<A>
extends Object
implements Iterable<A>
    This class implements polymorphic persistent lists. Instances of persistent lists are built mainly by adding an element in front of an existing list with cons(Object, PList), starting from the empty list empty(). They are immutable and allow (thread-)safe physical sharing of suffixes.

    This implementation allows null elements, in other words the type of elements A can be Nullable.
